  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "Chef likes problems related to learning new languages. He only knows first **N** letters of English alphabet. Also he explores all **M**-letter words formed by the characters he knows. Define cost for a given **M**-letter word **S**, cost(**S**) = **P1, S1+P2, S2+...+P**M**, SM**, where **Pi, j** is **i, j**th entry of matrix **P**. Sort all the words by descending cost, if costs are equal, sort them lexicographically. You need to find **K**-th **M**-letter word in Chef's order.",
    "constraints": [
      "1 ≤ **N** ≤ 16",
      "1 ≤ **M** ≤ 10",
      "1 ≤ **K** ≤ **NM**",
      "0 ≤ **Pi, j** ≤ 109",
      "Subtasks",
      "**Subtask #1: (20 points)** 1 ≤ **K** ≤ **10000**",
      "**Subtask #2: (20 points)** 1 ≤ **M** ≤ **5**",
      "**Subtask #3: (60 points)** Original constraints",
      "Example**Input:**",
      "2 5 17",
      "7 9",
      "13 18",
      "10 12",
      "4 18",
      "3 9",
      "**Output:**",
      "aaaba"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "First line contains three positive integer numbers **N**, **M** and **K**.\n\nNext **M** lines contains **N** integers per line, denoting the matrix **P**.",
    "outputFormat": "Output in a single line **K**-th **M**-letter in Chef's order.",
